# dist/ is committed so consumers installing via `npm install
# github:rprovine/kanai-pricing` work even when their npm doesn't
# run the `prepare` lifecycle (older npm, frozen lockfiles, etc.).
# The `prepare` script still rebuilds it on every install, but
# committing keeps the package usable as a pure git dependency.
